House Resolution 9
By: Representative Moore of the 91st
A RESOLUTION
1 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the State of Georgia so as to provide that
2 revenue derived from the regulation of safe drinking water and toxic enforcement may be
3 dedicated for certain purposes and not deposited into the general fund; to authorize the
4 General Assembly to create the Safe Drinking Water and Toxic Enforcement Fund; to
5 provide that such funds shall not lapse; to provide for related matters; to provide for the
6 submission of this amendment for ratification or rejection; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Article III, Section IX of the Constitution is amended in Paragraph VI by adding a new
10 subparagraph to read as follows:
11 "(s) The General Assembly may provide by general law for the creation of the Safe
12 Drinking Water and Toxic Enforcement Fund from which funds shall be disbursed for the
13 enforcement of laws regarding the protection of the citizens of this state from carcinogens
14 and toxic substances in drinking water and the protection of the citizens of this state from
15 exposure to carcinogens and toxic substances by businesses in the course of doing business.
16 The General Assembly shall be authorized to dedicate and deposit revenues raised from
17 specified sources to the fund and shall be authorized to appropriate other funds to the fund.
